---

## Experimental Results

### Average F1 Score Improvement

| Generator | Best Candidate | TransCausNet |
|------------|---------------|--------------|
| PC | 0.4192 | **0.4490** |
| GES | 0.3829 | **0.4455** |
| NOTEARS | 0.3913 | **0.4250** |
| DAGMA | 0.4212 | **0.4478** |
| KDB | 0.4161 | **0.4682** |

Results show consistent improvements over individual candidate DAGs through attention-based integration.

---

## Why TransCausNet?

Traditional approaches:

```text
Data
  ↓
Learn One DAG
  ↓
Output
```

TransCausNet:

```text
Data
  ↓
Generate Multiple DAGs
  ↓
Learn Which Ones To Trust
  ↓
Aggregate Through Transformer
  ↓
Better Global DAG
```

This provides:

- Higher robustness
- Better scalability
- Lower SHD
- Improved F1 score
- Better handling of noisy candidate graphs

